The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 07 January is 23,368 (2,704.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 02 January, there were 5,862 new confirmed cases (678.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 26 December, there were 3,036 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 93% (2,826 extra cases).
